\begin_layout Standard
There are time shifts
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
time!shifts
\end_layout

\end_inset

 inherent in many of the measurements, and in some cases (e.g., those produced
 by inertial reference units) these time shifts arise because the information
 is transmitted from the measuring system at a time later than when it was
 sampled.
 In these cases, shifts (
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

lags
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

) are applied to the measurements.
 The lags
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
lags in sampling
\end_layout

\end_inset

 may be either static or dynamic.
 Static lags
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
