 to the time it was actually acquired.
 e.g.
 for a 5hz parameter the expected or gridded millisecond offset into each
 second would be 0, 200, 400, 600, and 800.
 If the data actually were sampled or acquired at 50, 250, 450, 650, and
 850 ms then the dynamic lag for this particular second would be -50 ms.
